### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

If component has only `afterRenderEffect`, it executes durning `detectChanges`. But if I add `resource`, `afterRenderEffect` executes some time after `detectChanges`. 

---

#### Only `afterRenderEffect`

```typescript
@Component({
    template: ``,
})
class TestComponent {
    constructor() {
        console.log(`constructor`);

        afterRenderEffect(() => {
            console.log(`afterRenderEffect`);
        });
    }
}

it(`test`, () => {
    const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(TestComponent);

    console.log(`detectChanges`);
    fixture.detectChanges();
    console.log(`after detectChanges`);
});
```

Output:
```
constructor
detectChanges
afterRenderEffect
after detectChanges
```

---

#### `afterRenderEffect` + `resource`

```typescript
@Component({
    template: ``,
})
class TestComponent {
    public readonly test = resource({
        loader: async () => Promise.resolve(`test`),
    });

    constructor() {
        console.log(`constructor`);

        afterRenderEffect(() => {
            console.log(`afterRenderEffect`);
        });
    }
}

it(`test`, () => {
    const fixture = TestBed.createComponent(TestComponent);

    console.log(`detectChanges`);
    fixture.detectChanges();
    console.log(`after detectChanges`);
});
```

Output:
```
constructor
detectChanges
after detectChanges
afterRenderEffect
```

---

